rea/uk/constit/447.htm|title=Politics Resources|date=1 May 1997|work=Election 1997|publisher=Politics Resources|accessdate=7 Jan 2011}}</ref><ref>C. Rallings & M. Thrasher, The Media Guide to the New Parliamentary Constituencies, p.142 (Plymouth: LGC Elections Centre, 1995)\n</ref>}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n|candidate  = [[Kenneth Clarke]]\n|votes  = 27,558\n|percentage  = 44.4\n|change  = \u221210.0\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Labour Party (UK)\n|candidate  = Jocelyn Pettitt\n|votes  = 22,503\n|percentage  = 36.2\n|change  = +13.0\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n|candidate  = Sam Boote\n|votes  = 8,851\n|percentage  = 14.3\n|change  = \u22125.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Referendum Party\n|candidate  = Catherine Chadd\n|votes  = 2,682\n|percentage  = 4.3\n|change  = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = UK Independence Party\n|candidate  = Joseph Moore\n|votes  = 403\n|percentage  = 0.7\n|change  = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n|party      = Natural Law Party\n|candidate  = Anna Miszewska\n|votes  = 115\n|percentage  = 0.2\n|change  = +0.0\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n|votes  = 5,055\n|percentage  = 8.2\n|change  = \u221223.0\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n|votes  = 62,112\n|percentage  = 78.8\n|change  = \u22124.2\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link|\n|winner     = Conservative Party (UK)\n|swing      = \u221211.5\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n{{Election box begin |\n|title=[[1992 United Kingdom general election|General election 1992]]: Rushcliffe<ref name=electoralcalculus1992>{{cite web|title=Election Data 1992|url=http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_1992ob.txt|publisher=[[Electoral Calculus]]|accessdate=18 October 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015054418/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electda