 1777 |publisher=Press of the New Era Printing Company |url=https://archive.org/details/pennsylvaniasoc00socigoog |year=1901 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/pennsylvaniasoc00socigoog/page/n26 20]\u201328|accessdate=January 7, 2016 |ref=cadwalader1901}}\n* Calloway, Colin G. ''The American Revolution in Indian Country: Crisis and Diversity in Native American Communities'' (Cambridge UP, 1995)\n* {{cite book |last=Campbell  |first=Thomas |title=Annals of Great Britain |publisher=Stevenson |year=1807 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WfgTAAAAQAAJ |ref=campbell}}\n* {{cite web |author=Don Jaun Carlos I |title=General Bernardo Galvez in the American Revolution |year=1979 |access-date= April 3, 2020 |url=http://www.thecajuns.com/galvezrw.htm |ref=carlos}}\n* {{cite book |last=Carp |first=E. Wayne |title=To Starve the Army at Pleasure: Continental Army Administration and American Political Culture, 1775-1783 |authorlink= |publisher=UNC Press Books |year=1990 |isbn=978-0-8078-4269-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DL66YCXMbZ8C |ref=carp1990}}\n* {{cite web |title=A Look Back ... Intelligence and the Committee of Secret Correspondence |publisher=U. S. Central Intelligence Agency |url=https://www.cia.gov/news-information/featured-story-archive/2011-featured-story-archive/intelligence-and-the-committee-of-secret-correspondence.html |year=2011 |access-date=April 4, 2020 |ref=cia}} <!-- ref>[[#cia|CIA, 2011, Historical Document]]</ref -->\n* Chambers, John Whiteclay II, ed. in chief. ''The Oxford Companion to American Military History''. [[Oxford University Press]], 1999. {{ISBN|0195071980}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Jonathan |first=Chandler |year= |date= |title=To become again our brethren': Desertion and community during the American Revolutionary War, 1775-83 |url=https://academic.oup.com/histres/article/90/248/363/5603609 |journal=Historical Research |publisher= Oxford University Press |volume=90 |issue=March 2017 |jstor= |pages=363\u2013380 |doi= |access-date=March 20, 2020 |ref=chandler}}\n* {{cite book |last=Ch\u00e1vez  |first=Thomas E. |title=Spain and the Independence of the United States: An Intrinsic Gift |authorlink= |publisher=UNM Press |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-8263-2795-6 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z96CAwAAQBAJ&vq=ireland |ref=chavez}}\n* {{cite book  |last=Christie |first=Ian R.  |last2=Labaree  |first2=Benjamin W. |title=Empire or independence, 1760-1776 |authorlink= |publisher=Phaidon Press |year=1976 |isbn=978-0-7148-1614-2 |url= |ref=christie}}\n* {{cite book |last=Chartrand |first=Ren\u00e9  |title=Gibraltar 1779\u20131783: The Great Siege |authorlink= |publisher=Bloomsbury USA |year=2006 |isbn=978-1-8417-6977-6 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JUQ8vgAACAAJ |ref=chartrand}}  \n* {{cite book |last=Coleman  |first=Terry |title=The Nelson Touch: The Life and Legend of Horatio Nelson |authorlink= |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2004 |isbn=978-0-1999-2405-9 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OiY8posT9hoC |ref=coleman}}\n* {{cite book |last=Clode |first=Charles M. |title=The military forces of the crown ; their administration and government |volume=1 |authorlink= |publisher=London, J. Murray |year=1869 |isbn= |url=https://archive.org/details/militaryforcesc02clodgoog/page/n4/mode/2up |ref=clode1869}}\n* {{cite book |last=Clode |first=Charles M. |title=The military forces of the crown ; their administration and government |volume=2|authorlink= |publisher=London, J. Murray |year=1869 |isbn= |url=https://archive.org/details/militaryforcesc00clodgoog/page/n7/mode/2up |ref=clode1869'v2}}\n* {{cite book |last=Clodfelter |first=Micheal |title=Warfare and Armed Conflicts: A Statistical Encyclopedia of Casualty and Other Figures, 1492-2015, 4th ed. |authorlink= |publisher=McFarland |year=2017 |isbn=978-1-4766-2585-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kNzCDgAAQBAJ |ref=clodfelter}}\n* Conway, Stephen. ''The British Isles and the War of American Independence'' (2002) {{DOI|10.1093/acprof:o