apman Publishers |year=1831 |isbn= |url=https://archive.org/details/lifeoflordnelson00sout_0/page/n2/mode/2up |ref=southey31}}\n* {{cite book |editor1-first=Jared |editor1-last=Sparks |last=Franklin |first=Benjamin |last2=Lee |first2=Arthur |last3=Adams |first3=John |title=The diplomatic correspondence of the American Revolution |volume=1 |authorlink= |publisher=Boston: Hale, Gray & Bowen |year=1829 |isbn= |url=https://archive.org/details/diplomaticcorres01sparuoft/page/n7/mode/2up/search/Portugal |ref=sparks1829}}\n* Stephenson, Orlando W. \"The Supply of Gunpowder in 1776\", ''American Historical Review'', 30#2 (1925), pp.&nbsp;271\u201381 [http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Journals/AHR/30/2/Supply_of_Gunpowder_in_1776.html online free]\n* {{cite book |last=Stockley |first=Andrew |title=Britain and France at the Birth of America: The European Powers and the Peace Negotiations of 1782-1783 |authorlink= |publisher=University of Exeter Press |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-8598-9615-3 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mHoaiPKTKvwC |ref=stockley2001}}\n<!-- T  -->\n* {{cite book |last=Taylor |first=Alan |title=American Revolutions: A Continental History, 1750\u20131804 |publisher=WW Norton & Company |year=2016 |isbn=978-0-3932-5387-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E92aCwAAQBAJ |ref=taylor2016}}\n* Tombs, Robert and Isabelle. ''That Sweet Enemy: The French and the British from the Sun King to the Present'' Random House, 2007. {{ISBN|9781400040247}}\n* {{cite web |first= |last= |title=Red Coats  |publisher=Totallyhistory.com |year=2012 |accessdate=March 23, 2020 |url=http://totallyhistory.com/red-coats/ |ref=redcoatsfacts}}\n* Trevelyan, George Otto. ''George the Third and Charles Fox: the concluding part of The American revolution'' Longmans, Green, 1912\n* {{cite book |last=Trew |first=Peter |title=Rodney and the Breaking of the Line |authorlink= |publisher=Pen & Sword Military |year=2006 |isbn=978-1-8441-5143-1 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5XfxAAAAMAAJ |ref=trew}} \n<!-- U  -->\n* {{cite web |first= |last= |title=Privateers and Mariners in the Revolutionary War |publisher=U.S. Merchant Marine |year=2012 |accessdate=May 25, 2017 |url=http://www.usmm.org/revolution.html |ref=usmm}}  <!-- ref>[[#usmm|U.S. Merchant Marine, 2012]]</ref -->\n<!-- V -->\n*  {{cite book |last= Volo |first= M. James |title=''Blue Water Patriots: The American Revolution Afloat |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield Publishers, Inc. |year=2008 |isbn=978-0-7425-6120-5 |url= |ref=volo}} \n\n<!-- W  -->\n* Watson, J. Steven. [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=22810670 ''The Reign of George III, 1760\u20131815'']. 1960. Standard history of British politics.\n* Weigley, Russell F. ''The American Way of War''. Indiana University Press, 1977. {{ISBN|9780253280299}}.\n* Weintraub, Stanley. ''Iron Tears: America's Battle for Freedom, Britain's Quagmire: 1775\u20131783''. New York: Free Press, 2005 (a division of Simon & Schuster). {{ISBN|0743226879}}. An account of the British politics on the conduct of the war\n* {{Cite journal |last=Whaples |first=Robert |author-link=Robert Whaples |journal=[[The Journal of Economic History]] |volume=55 |issue=1 |page=144 |jstor=2123771 |title=Where Is There Consensus Among American Economic Historians? The Results of a Survey on Forty Propositions |date=March 1995 |doi=10.1017/S0022050700040602| quote=There is an overwhelming consensus that Americans' economic standard of living on the eve of the Revolution was among the highest in the world. |citeseerx=10.1.1.482.4975 |ref=whaples}}\n* {{cite web |last=White |first=Matthew |year=2010 |url= http://necrometrics.com/wars18c.htm#AmRev |title= Spanish casualties in The American Revolutionary war |publisher= Necrometrics |ref=necro}}</ref>\n* {{cite book |first=Willard M. |last=Wallace  |title=Traitorous Hero: The Life and Fortunes of Benedict Arnold |publisher=New York: Harper & Brothers |year=1954 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=y192AAAAMAAJ |ref=wallace54}}\n