/14306387 | archivedate = November 15, 2012}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| South Korea ([http://gaonchart.co.kr/ Gaon Chart])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=week&hitYear=2016&targetTime=13&nationGbn=E|title=GAON Chart|publisher= GAON|date=March 31, 2016|accessdate=March 31, 2016}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakia|10|artist=Shakira|song=Try Everything|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 15, 2016|year=2016|week=42}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakdigital|50|artist=Shakira|song=Try Everything|rowheader=true|accessdate=July 4, 2016|year=2016|week=26}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Slovenia ([[SloTop50]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slotop50.si/Glasbene-lestvice/Tedenske-lestvice/?year=2016&week=26|title=SloTop50 \u2013 Slovenian official singles chart|publisher=slotop50.si|accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref>\n| 39\n|-\n{{singlechart|Spain|32|artist=Shakira|song=Try Everything|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|39|artist=Shakira|song=Try Everything|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK Singles ([[Official Charts Company]])<ref>{{cite web|title=CHART: CLUK Update 9.04.2016 (wk14)|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/160409cluk.txt|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=April 15, 2016}}</ref>\n| 186\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|63|artist=Shakira|accessdate=March 22, 2016|rowheader=true}}\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2016)\n!Position\n|-\n|South Korean [[Gaon Music Chart]]<ref>{{cite web |title=2016 South Korean Gaon Music Singles Chart |url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?serviceGbn=ALL&termGbn=year&hitYear=2016&targetTime=2016&nationGbn=E |publisher=[[Gaon Music Chart]] |accessdate=24 March 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|51\n|-\n|Taiwan Hit Fm Top Annual Top 100 Singles <ref>{{cite web |title=Hit Fm Top Yearly Top 100 Singles |url=http://www.hitoradio.com/newweb/chart_2.php?ch_year=2016&pageNum_rsList=1 |publisher=[[Hit FM (Taiwan)]] |accessdate=20 June 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|74\n|-\n|}\n\n==Sales and certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=South Korea ([[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon]])|relyear=2016|certyear=0|artist=Shakira|title=Try Everything|award={{n/a}}|certref=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/|title=Gaon Chart|publisher=Gaon Chart}}</ref>|type=single|certmonth=5|salesamount=253,018^|access-date=March 28, 2016}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|title=Try Everything|artist=Shakira|type=single|award=Silver|relyear=2016|certyear=2019|access-date=13 November 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|title=Try Everything|artist=Shakira|type=single|award=Platinum|number=2|certyear=2019|digital=true|access-date=27 June 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|noshipments=true|streaming=true}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.metrolyrics.com/try-everything-lyrics-shakira.html Full lyrics of this song] at [[MetroLyrics]].\n{{Shakira songs}}\n\n[[Category:2016 songs]]\n[[Category:Shakira songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written for animated films]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sia (musician)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mikkel Storleer Eriksen]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Tor Erik Hermansen]]\n[[Category:Disney songs]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Records singles]]\n[[Category:2016 singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Stargate (production team)]]\n[[Category:2010s ballads]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the Republica song|Speed Ballads}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Try Everything\n| cover      = Try_Everything_(Shakira).jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shakira]]\n| album      = [[Zootopia#Soundtrack|Zootopia]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2016|02|15}}\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = November 2015<br>[[Westlake Recording Studios]]\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = \n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=22}}\n| label      = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Sia Furler]]|[[Stargate (production team)|Tor Hermansen]]|[[Stargate (production team)|Mikkel Eriksen]]}}\n| producer   = [[Stargate (production team)|Stargate]]\n| prev_title = [[Mi Verdad (song)|Mi Verdad]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title = [[La Bicicleta]]\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|c6rP-YP4c5I|\"Try Everything\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Try Everything'''\" is a song recorded by Colombian singer [[Shakira]] for the 2016 [[Walt Disney Animation Studios]] film ''[[Zootopia]]'', and written by [[Sia Furler]], [[Stargate (production team)|Tor Hermansen]], and [[Stargate (production team)|Mikkel Eriksen]].\n\nIn the film, it is featured as a song recorded by a singer named Gazelle (voiced by Shakira). It is first heard when Judy Hopps plays it on her MP3 player on the train to Zootopia, and is heard again during the end credits. The song appears on the soundtrack album to ''Zootopia'', and was released as a single during February 2016.\n\n==Commercial Performance==\nThe song debuted and peaked at number 63 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7263821/hot-100-chart-moves-meghan-trainor-shakira-debut|title=Hot 100 Chart Moves: Meghan Trainor & Shakira Debut, Taylor Swift & Justin Bieber Return|access-date=July 14, 2016}}</ref> as well as number 26 on the Digital Songs chart with the help of 33,000 digital downloads and three million US streams after the release of its official music video.<ref>Trust, Gary (March 18, 2016). [http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7263821/hot-100-chart-moves-meghan-trainor-shakira-debut \"Hot 100 Chart Moves: Meghan Trainor & Shakira Debut, Taylor Swift & Justin Bieber Return]. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Retrieved March 19, 2016.</ref> The song was certified 2 times platinum in the [[United States]] by [[RIAA]] for sales exceeding 2,000,000 units, it also received a silver certification in the [[United Kingdom]] by [[BPI]] for sales of over 200,000 units.\n\n==Critical Reception==\nThe song was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media|Best Song Written For Visual Media]] at the [[59th Annual Grammy Awards|59th Grammy Awards]].\nIn 2020 ''[[Billboard (magazine)| Billboard]]'' named ''\"Try Everything\"'' as one of the 12 best [[Disney]] songs of the 21st century.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9358357/disney-best-songs-21st-century|title=Disney's 12 Best Songs of the 21st Century: Critic's Picks|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video consists mostly of scenes from ''Zootopia'', intercut with footage of Shakira singing in a recording studio.\n\n== Other languages ==\nBeing only a background song, not key for the understanding of the plot, ''Try Everything'' was left untranslated in most foreign dubs. However, it has a few adaptations around the world.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" |All official versions of \"Try Everything\"\n|-\n!Language\n!Performer\n!Title \n!Translation\n|-\n|[[Standard Chinese|Chinese Mandarin]]\n|\u4e5d\u4e5d (Sophie Chen)<ref>{{Citation|last=jjy728|title=\u4e5d\u4e5d -\u300a\u5617\u8a66\u4e00\u5207\u300bMV (\u52d5\u756b\u52d5\u7269\u65b9\u57ce\u5e02\u4e3b\u984c\u66f2)|date=March 24, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IqBDXlU6qAU|accessdate=July 1, 2016}}</ref>\n|\"\u5c1d\u8bd5\u4e00\u5207\" (\"Ch\u00e1ng sh\u00ec y\u012b qi\u00e8\")\n|\"Try everything\"\n|-\n|[[English language|English]]\n|[[Shakira]]\n| colspan=\"2\" |\"Try everything\"\n|-\n|[[Hindi]]\n|\u0936\u094d\u0930\u0941\u0924\u093f \u0930\u093e\u0923\u0947 (Shruti Rane)\n|\"\u0939\u093e\u0930 \u0928\u093e \u092e\u093e\u0928\u0942\u0901\u0917\u0940\" (\"Haar na Manungi\")\n|\"I won't give up\"\n|-\n|[[Japanese language|Japanese]]\n|[[Dream Ami]]<ref>{{Citation|last=avex|title=Dream Ami / \u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30fb\u30a8\u30f4\u30ea\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0 (Dream Ami version)|date=March 31, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EIunkyaaRII|accessdate=July 1, 2016}}</ref>\n|\"\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30fb\u30a8\u30f4\u30ea\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\" (\"Torai evurishingu\")\n|\"Try everything\"\n|-\n|[[Korean language|Korean]]\n|\uae40\uacbd\uc120 (Kim Kyung-Sun)<ref>{{Citation|last=ssiah02_re|title=Zootopia - Try Everything (Korean / LQ / HQ link)|date=February 29, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wyl50aNL7xY|accessdate=July 1, 2016}}</ref>\n|\"\ucd5c\uc120\uc744 \ub2e4\ud574\" (\"Choiseon-eul dahae\")\n|\"Do your best\"\n|-\n|[[Polish language|Polish]]\n|{{Interlanguage link multi|Paulina Przybysz|pl}}<ref>{{Citation|last=DisneyPolskaVEVO|title=Paulina Przybysz - Nie b\u00f3j sie chciec (z filmu \"Zwierzogr\u00f3d\" (Official Video))|date=April 13, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QOSoCmcR0Ms|accessdate=July 1, 2016}}</ref>\n|\"Nie b\u00f3j si\u0119 chcie\u0107\"\n|\"Don\u2019t be afraid of wishing\"\n|-\n|[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]]\n|[[Zlata Ognevich|\u0417\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u041e\u0433\u043d\u0454\u0432\u0456\u0447 (Zlata Ognevich)]]<ref>{{Citation|last=Gravity|title=Zootopia \u2014 Try Everything (Ukrainian) [Zlata Ognevich]|date=April 3, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6om0njaFnBE|accessdate=July 1, 2016}}</ref>\n|\"\u041d\u0435 \u0432\u0456\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043b\u044e\" (\"Ne vidstuplyu\")\n|\"I won't give up\"\n|}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2016)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2016/07/chart-watch-376/|title=CHART WATCH #376|publisher=auspOp|date=